3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"OKX calculates ETHFI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC, based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange uses a time-weighted average price methodology with a ±0.75% funding rate cap. Portfolio margin mode allows cross-collateralization with other positions, reducing margin requirements for sophisticated arbitrage strategies. Settlement occurs automatically for all open positions at funding timestamps."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ETHFI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI represents exposure to Ether.fi's liquid staking ecosystem, creating unique funding dynamics driven by ETH staking narratives and DeFi yield trends. The pair's smaller volume on OKX can lead to more pronounced funding rate deviations compared to major tokens. This creates arbitrage windows, especially during periods of high volatility in the liquid staking derivatives sector."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI/USDT funding rates on OKX have shown elevated volatility since the token's launch, with rates frequently exceeding ±0.3% per 8-hour cycle during DeFi narrative-driven moves. Positive funding dominates during ETH staking yield optimizations and liquid staking token rallies, while negative rates emerge during broader DeFi sector corrections. The pair typically exhibits higher rate volatility than established DeFi tokens due to lower liquidity and newer market dynamics. Weekend periods often show reduced funding rate compression as institutional activity decreases."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between OKX and larger venues like Binance can be profitable when ETHFI funding rates diverge significantly, typically by >0.15% per cycle. Delta-neutral strategies work effectively by holding spot ETHFI while shorting perpetuals during high positive funding periods. OKX's portfolio margin system enables capital-efficient arbitrage by using USDT, ETH, or BTC as cross-collateral. Advanced traders can combine ETHFI positions with related DeFi tokens like LDO to create sector-neutral funding rate harvesting strategies."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ETHFI's correlation with ETH staking narratives creates concentrated risk during protocol-specific events like validator updates or staking reward changes. Lower liquidity compared to major perpetuals increases slippage risk during position management, especially for larger arbitrage sizes. The token's newer market status means historical funding patterns may not predict future behavior during market stress periods. Smart contract risks from the underlying Ether.fi protocol, though minimal for perpetual trading, should be considered for comprehensive risk assessment."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical ETHFI funding rates on OKX?","answer":"ETHFI funding rates on OKX typically range from -0.2% to +0.4% per 8-hour cycle, with higher volatility than established tokens. During DeFi sector rallies, positive rates can hit the +0.75% cap, while corrections may drive rates negative for extended periods."},{"question":"How does OKX's portfolio margin affect ETHFI arbitrage?","answer":"Portfolio margin mode allows using multiple cryptocurrencies as collateral for ETHFI positions, reducing capital requirements by up to 80% compared to isolated margin. This enables more efficient delta-neutral strategies and cross-exchange arbitrage with lower funding costs."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for ETHFI funding arbitrage on OKX?","answer":"OKX's minimum order size for ETHFI perpetuals is typically 1 ETHFI, but effective arbitrage strategies generally require positions of at least 100-500 ETHFI to overcome trading fees and funding rate volatility."},{"question":"How does ETHFI funding compare to other liquid staking tokens?","answer":"ETHFI funding rates show higher volatility than established liquid staking derivatives like stETH-related products, offering potentially higher arbitrage returns but with increased risk from lower liquidity and newer market dynamics."}]}]
